Player stats are fun stats that you can add and display for relatively 
any event on DarkWind. 

One rule of thumb: keep the player stats fun and light hearted. Don't
use pstats to expose some underlying bit of information that may
give other players tactical advantages against that player in PK.

Adding player stats are really easy to do, also! 

Here's how:

1. Update /secure/include/playerstats.h to add your new stat. For
   example, let's say we want to track every time a user uses the
   spell "entangle". 

   First, we'd add this to the playerstats.h file:


#define CAST_ENTANGLE       "cast_entangle"


   The important thing here is to make sure that "cast_entangle" is
   unique, and not used by any other stats in this header file.

   NOTE: If you are adding a guild stat, please group it under the
   appropriate area with that guild's other stats!


2. Update the PLAYER_STATS_STRING mapping at the bottom of the header 
   file.




CAST_ENTANGLE : "Entangle Spell Cast"; "Druid", \




   This defines the label for this stat to be "Entangle Spell Cast",
   and for it to be grouped within "Druid Stats" when displayed on
   pstats.


3. Now update your code where that actual event happens, and put in 
   the hook:

#include <daemons.h>
#include <playerstats.h>




PLAYER_STATS_D->increment_stat(this_player()->query_real_name(), 
        CAST_ENTANGLE);





4. And, finally, assuming your code from step 3 updates, update the
   /cmds/std/_pstats.c command for it to pick up the newly added
   stat!


You're good to go! Your new stat is now implemented!


See also: 9.15.1

